  "body": "Have been using buidler with `Ganache CLI v6.4.3 (ganache-core: 2.5.5)` and its gas estimation is wildly off - much lower than necessary. Because the V5 plugin relies on truffle-contract's gas estimation by default lots of calls fail. There are no problems when geth is the client. \r\n\r\nAs a workaround I set a network with a gas value:\r\n```\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  solc: { version: \"0.5.5\" },\r\n  networks: {\r\n    'development': {\r\n      gas: 7000000\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n}\r\n```\r\n[Edit]\r\n```\r\nnpx buidler test --network development\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nWhile debugging this I tried using a higher `gasMultiplier` in the config while logging the result in `getGasEstimate` at truffle-contract and it seemed like that option isn't being set. It's always 1.25. Not sure if this is a truffle bug or an issue here. ",
